-- JPMorgan has bought back more stock in 2nd qtr than expected - CFO
-- By David Henry in New York
-- Wed Jun 11, 2014 09:04AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, June 11 (Reuters) - JPMorgan Chase & Co <JPM.N> has bought back more of its own stock in the second quarter than it had expected, Chief Financial Officer Marianne Lake said on Wednesday.

Speaking at an investor conference in New York, Lake said the purchases were greater than the amount of shares issued to pay employees and that the company had stayed on track to reach its capital goals despite the additional spending. She did not say exactly how much stock the company had bought back.